openChannel

public Channel openChannel(java.lang.String clientId)
Opens an AppEngine Channel for the given clientId. Looks for an existing entry in the datastore for clientId, and if found opens a channel for that client. If no existing channel is found, it creates a new one to return.

Parameters:
clientId - The client for which we are opening a Channel.
Returns:
A Channel object populated with the clientId, and token, as well as subscriberIds and a TV Code, if present.

subscribe

public Channel subscribe(java.lang.String childClientId,
                         java.lang.String parentClientId)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
Subscribes two clients to each other, allowing two-way communication.

Looks up the parentClientId and adds the childClientId as a subscriber. The it does the opposite, adding the parent as a subscriber to the child. This allows two-way communication.

Parameters:
childClientId - The id of the client initiating the request. This would typically be a mobile device's clientId
parentClientId - The id of the client being subscribe to. This would typically be a TV's clientId
Returns:
The Channel object of the childClientId.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception
